HEADWORD: Laster
<hw>Last"er</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A workman whose business it is to
shape boots or shoes, or place leather smoothly, on lasts; a tool for
stretching leather on a last.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lastery</ent>⟦br⟧
